column.description: Grouping tile used to organize tiles into a column without a border around it.

concatenation.description: A concatenation is a line of text made up of multiple, concatenated text_part tiles.

dialog.description: A dialog is the tile that defines the dialog box.

edit_box.signature: : edit_box { action alignment allow_accept edit_limit edit_width fixed_height fixed_width height is_enabled is_tab_stop key label mnemonic value width password_char }
edit_box.description: An edit box is a field that enables the user to enter or edit a single line of text.

errtile.description: An error tile is a text tile that appears at the bottom of a dialog box.

image.signature: : image { action alignment aspect_ratio color fixed_height fixed_width height is_enabled is_tab_stop key mnemonic value width }
image.description: An image is a rectangle in which a vector graphic picture is displayed.

image_button.signature: : image_button { action alignment allow_accept aspect_ratio color fixed_height fixed_width height is_enabled is_tab_stop key mnemonic width }
image_button.description: The image button tile is a button that displays a graphic image rather than a label.

list_box.signature: : list_box { action alignment allow_accept fixed_height fixed_width fixed_width_font height is_enabled is_tab_stopkey label list mnemonic multiple_select tab_truncate tabs value width }
list_box.description: A list box contains a list of text strings, arranged in rows.

ok_cancel.description: The ok_cancel tile is a combination of the OK and Cancel buttons, and is the standard combination for dialog boxes that can originate changes to data.

ok_cancel_help.description: This tile is the ok_cancel cluster combined with the Help button.

ok_cancel_help_errtile.description: The ok_cancel_help_errtile tile provides a convenient way to specify the exit buttons and error tile all at once.

ok_cancel_help_info.description: The ok_cancel_help_info tile does everything that the ok_cancel_help tile does, but it also includes an information button for displaying additional material.

ok_only.description: The ok_only tile is a solitary OK button, such as the kind that alert boxes use.

paragraph.description: A paragraph is a cluster of text_part or concatenation tiles that are arranged vertically.

popup_list.signature: : popup_list { action alignment edit_width fixed_height fixed_width fixed_width_font height is_enabled is_tab_stop key label list mnemonic tab_truncate tabs value width }
popup_list.description: A pop-up list, or simply pop-up, is functionally equivalent to a list box.

radio_button.signature: : radio_button { action alignment fixed_height fixed_width height is_enabled is_tab_stop key label mnemonic value width }
radio_button.description: A radio button is one of a group of buttons composing a radio column or radio row.

radio_column.signature: : radio_column { alignment children_alignment children_fixed_height children_fixed_width fixed_height fixed_width height label width }
radio_column.description: A radio column contains radio button tiles, only one of which can be selected at a time.

radio_row.signature: : radio_row { alignment children_alignment children_fixed_height children_fixed_width fixed_height fixed_width height label width }
radio_row.description: A radio row, like a radio column, contains radio button tiles, only one of which can be selected at a time.

row.signature: : row { alignment children_alignment children_fixed_height children_fixed_width fixed_height fixed_width height label width }
row.description: Grouping tile used to organize tiles into a row without a border around it.

slider.signature: : slider { action alignment big_increment fixed_height fixed_width height key label layout max_value min_value mnemonic small_increment value width }
slider.description: A slider obtains a numeric value.

spacer.signature: : spacer { alignment fixed_height fixed_width height width }
spacer.description: Tile used to add space between other tiles in a dialog definition.

spacer_0.description: Tile used to add space between other tiles in a dialog definition.

spacer_1.description: Tile used to add space between other tiles in a dialog definition.

text.signature: : text { alignment fixed_height fixed_width height is_bold key label value width }
text.description: A text tile displays a text string for titling or informational purposes.

text_part.description: A text part is a text tile that is part of a larger piece of text.

toggle.signature: : toggle { action alignment fixed_height fixed_width height is_enabled is_tab_stop label width }
toggle.description: A toggle appears as a small box with an optional label to the right of the box.

activate.description: Triggered when a document window is activated.

appactivate.description: Triggered just before the main application window is activated.

appdeactivate.description: Triggered just before the main application window is deactivated.

arxloaded.description: Triggered when an ObjectARX application has been loaded.

arxunloaded.description: Triggered when an ObjectARX application has been unloaded.

beginclose.description: Triggered immediately after AutoCAD receives a request to close a drawing.

begincommand.description: Triggered immediately after a command is issued, but before it completes.

begindocclose.description: Triggered immediately after AutoCAD receives a request to close a drawing.

begindoubleclick.description: Triggered after the user double-clicks an object in the drawing.

beginfiledrop.description: Triggered when a file is dropped on the main application window.

beginlisp.description: Triggered immediately after AutoCAD receives a request to evaluate an AutoLISP expression.

beginmodal.description: Triggered just before a modal dialog is displayed.

beginopen.description: Triggered immediately after AutoCAD receives a request to open an existing drawing.

beginplot.description: Triggered immediately after AutoCAD receives a request to print a drawing.

beginquit.description: Triggered just before an AutoCAD session ends or a document closes.

beginrightclick.description: Triggered after the user right-clicks on the drawing window.

beginsave.description: Triggered immediately after AutoCAD receives a request to save the drawing.

beginshortcutmenucommand.description: Triggered after the user right-clicks on the drawing window, and before the shortcut menu appears in command mode.

beginshortcutmenudefault.description: Triggered after the user right-clicks on the drawing window, and before the shortcut menu appears in default mode.

beginshortcutmenuedit.description: Triggered after the user right-clicks on the drawing window, and before the shortcut menu appears in edit mode.

beginshortcutmenugrip.description: Triggered after the user right-clicks on the drawing window, and before the shortcut menu appears in grip mode.

beginshortcutmenuosnap.description: Triggered after the user right-clicks on the drawing window, and before the shortcut menu appears in object snap mode.

deactivate.description: Triggered when the drawing window is deactivated.

endcommand.description: Triggered immediately after a command completes.

endlisp.description: Triggered upon completion of evaluating an AutoLISP expression.

endmodal.description: Triggered just after a modal dialog is dismissed.

endopen.description: Triggered immediately after AutoCAD finishes opening an existing drawing.

endplot.description: Triggered after a document has been sent to the printer.

endsave.description: Triggered when AutoCAD has finished saving the drawing.

endshortcutmenu.description: Triggered after the shortcut menu appears.

layoutswitched.description: Triggered after the user switches to a different layout.

lispcancelled.description: Triggered when the evaluation of a AutoLISP expression is cancelled.

modified.description: Triggered when an object or collection in the drawing has been modified.

newdrawing.description: Triggered just before a new drawing is created.

objectadded.description: Triggered when an object has been added to the drawing.

objecterased.description: Triggered when an object has been erased from the drawing.

objectmodified.description: Triggered when an object in the drawing has been modified.

selectionchanged.description: Triggered when the current pickfirst selection set changes.

sysvarchanged.description: Triggered when the value of a system variable is changed.

windowchanged.description: Triggered when there is a change to the application or document windows.

windowmovedorresized.description: Triggered just after the application or drawing window has been moved or resized.
